5|$|However, despite Ohio's large {{presence}} in the iron and steel market, employment rates have declined in Ohio, generally attributed to weakening national economy. Between 1998 and 2005, the number of Ohio <b>iron</b> <b>and</b> <b>steel</b> <b>industry</b> workers decreased from 52,700 to 34,000. The Ohio Department of Development predicts the decreases will continue in coming years. The average annual salary for <b>iron</b> <b>and</b> <b>steel</b> <b>industry</b> workers in Ohio was $59,686, compared the national industry average of $53,352.|$|E
