50|$|In the past, Farciennes was an {{industrial}} city. It declined with {{the closure of}} the last Walloon coal mine, namely the Sainte-Catherine shaft of the Roton company, and the fall of the <b>iron</b> <b>and</b> <b>steel</b> <b>industries,</b> formerly large employers in the area between Liège and Charleroi. Today, the site of Roton, of which only the tower and the cloakroom remain, has been developed to accommodate small and medium-sized businesses.|$|R
